    <text id="B1196T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Trout, the mayor of Staunton, states his agreement with John Watts' request that
                    Roswell Waldo remain stationed as the Bureau's agent in Staunton, and not be
                    relocated.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="General">Genl</abbr> O. Brown <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> &amp;c</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-10-25"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 25 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="General">Genl</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have read the foregoing letter of <unclear>Maj.</unclear> Watts I concur in the
                        <unclear>sentiments</unclear> he has made and believe that the public
                    interest will be much promoted by the retention of Mr. Waldo at this post of
                    duty, and hope that it may meet the approbation of the appointing power to
                    revoke the order sending him elsewhere.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>N. K. Trout<lb/>Mayor of Staunton</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
